HEADWORD: Puerility
<hw>Pu`er*il"i*ty</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>; <plu><it>pl.</it>
<plw>Puerilities</plw> <pr>(#)</pr>.</plu> <ety>[L.
<ets>puerilitas</ets>: cf. F. <ets>pu⟦eacute⟧rilit⟦eacute⟧</ets>.]</ety>
<sn>1.</sn> <def>The quality of being puerile; childishness;
puerileness.</def> <rj><au>Sir T. Browne.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>That which is puerile or childish; especially, an
expression which is flat, insipid, or silly.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Puerperal</ent>⟦br⟧
